author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
cuisine: Asian
---

Very thinly slice the @Pork Medallion{500%g} widthways into ½cm slices. LH: toss
them in the @Cornflour{2%tbsp} with a pinch of @salt{} and a few grinds of @black
pepper{}.

Boil @water{700%ml} with @salt{1/2%tsp} in a #pot{}. Once the water comes to a
boil turn the heat to the lowest setting. Add the @Basmati Rice{2%servings} and
place a tight lid on the pot. Leave on the lowest heat for ~{10%minutes}, then
remove from the heat for ~{10%minutes}.

> Don't peek under the lid for 20 mins or the rice won't be perfect!

Peel and very finely chop the @garlic{2%cloves}. Peel the skin from the
@ginger{2cm} using the edge of a #spoon{} and then finely chop or grate it.
Remove the core from the @green pepper{2} and slice lengthways into ½cm slices.
Peel and chop the @carrot{2} into ½cm sticks (thinner if your knife skills
allow!). Finally, chop the @spring onion{3} widthways into really thin discs
then separate the white and green parts.

Put a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat and add the @cashew nuts{2%tbsp}
(without oil). Cook the cashew nuts until they have turned brown and then
remove them from the pan.

> Watch your nuts like a Wimbledon line judge as the moment your back is turned
  they'll burn!

Once the nuts are removed add @oil{2%tsp} to the pan and turn the heat to high.
Once it's really hot, carefully lay in half of the pork pieces. Cook the slices
for ~{1%minute} on each side then remove, repeat with the remaining pork slices.

> We cook in two batches as overcrowding the pan will stew your meat rather
  than brown it.

Add @oil{1%tsp} to the pan together with the pepper and carrot sticks. Cook for
~{4%minutes} before adding the whites of the spring onion, garlic and ginger.
Cook for ~{30%seconds} and then put your pork back in the pan.

Add the @Black Bean Sauce{2%tbsp} together with @water{4%tbsp} and toss
everything together for ~{1%minute}, before serving it with your rice, a
sprinkle of cashews and the greens of the spring onion.